Be an advisor and a subject matter resource for reputation, quality and risk management matters, and provide sound, practical and timely advice to Tax & Legal (T&L) personnel in Vietnam and other countries in Southeast Asia.
Key responsibilities include:
• Work with Vietnam T&L Business Leader and Risk Group, Southeast Asia (SEA) T&L Quality & Risk Leader and Team to execute quality and risk plan and strategies, and where required, execution of SEA and Asia Pacific quality and risk initiatives;
• Develop and foster a consultation network and intelligent risk culture within the T&L practice in Vietnam and SEA;
• Assist to develop policy, processes, tools and templates to enable T&L professionals in Vietnam and SEA to work efficiently and effectively to deliver client engagements while maintaining compliance with reputation and risk management policies, as well as legal and regulatory requirements;
• Provide consultation on queries raised by Vietnam and SEA T&L personnel on timely manner;
• Review legal documents on daily basis such as contracts, NDA, engagement letters, bidding documents, as well as communicate with clients’ legal team and manage arising contractual risks;
• Review client and engagement acceptance and risk assessment process on daily basis;
• Conducting internal practice review, inflight reviews, spot checks on T&L personnel compliance to the internal policies.
• Tracking and monitoring of T&L personnel compliance to Firm’s policies, evaluate non-compliances under disciplinary policies and issuing warning letters;
• Deliver risk management learning programs to Vietnam and SEA T&L professionals;
• Other tasks where required, to support the T&L quality and risk program.

Work you’ll do
• Assist Managers and above in performing GES engagements with the focus on Immigration services, Personal Income Tax, Payroll services and other required engagements would also be open for discussion;
• Assist in preparing proposals and business development materials, identifying potential service opportunities and approaching strategic accounts;
• Assist in developing standardization processes to improve efficiency and ensure risk management;
• Work independently and collaborate well with team members to prepare accurate working papers and/or concise and well-written reports using appropriate business and technical knowledge on a timely basis;
• Instruct staffs below to conduct research, analyse issues and draft advice related to clients’ issues focusing on Immigration (focus), Payroll, Labour and Social insurance (if any) and ensure quality of work delivered to Managers;
• Proactively get involved in working with the vendors/ government authorities to ensure a smooth working process;
• Provide timely guidance and direct feedback and mentorship that contribute to the ongoing development of the staffs in the team;
• Provide frequent internal trainings/updates to team members;
• Develop and maintain distinct relationships with peers at client organizations/ government authorities.

